{"id":"8746","name":"Archive, Backup and Restore Shortcuts","tagline":"Archive, Backup and Restore (previously archived or backed up) Shortcuts","icon":"ios14 c463140863 g61440","latest":"26434","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Title says it all. After loosing all my (previously backed up) Shortcuts due to iCloud sync issues and user error, and then running into challenges trying to restore a backup (didn't work because iOS 14.4.x can't restore nor import from a file), I've decided to make lives easier for everyone.\nA minor modification will allow for scheduling regular backups using Shortcuts' Automations.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>2.0 - March 27, 2021, 11:43 p.m.</strong></p><p>Modified the shortcuts so that it can now be passed a command that drives one of the 4 actions (Archive Shortcuts, Restore from Archive, Backup all Shortcuts and Restore from Backup. This way the Shortcut can be used in iOS Automations, especially when using it for re-occuring backups. When using in an automation, you'll want to pass in a Dictionary with a Key called \"Command\" and its value being one of the 4 actions (for example, \"Backup All Shortcuts\").</p>"}